ggestionType \\\"PLAN_RECOMMENDATION\\\". Set the prompt to the serialized risk+calibration context and the suggestionPayload to the JSON-serialized recommendation. The returned AiSuggestion.getId() becomes the PlanRecommendation.suggestionId.\\n       7. Return empty list when no risks detected.\\n    b. List<PlanRecommendation> getRecommendations(UUID planId) — the retrieval method. Reads persisted PLAN_RECOMMENDATION rows from AiSuggestionRepository.findByPlanIdAndSuggestionType(planId, \\\"PLAN_RECOMMENDATION\\\"), deserializes each row's suggestionPayload back into PlanRecommendation (with the row's id as suggestionId). Returns stable IDs across repeated calls — no regeneration, no new rows.\\n  - The GET endpoint calls getRecommendations() (read-only). A separate POST endpoint or an explicit ?refresh=true query param triggers generateAndPersistRecommendations(). This ensures the suggestionId is stable across page loads and refetches, making localStorage-based dismissal and AiFeedbackButtons reliable.\\n  - Graceful degradation: if WhatIfService or CalibrationService fails, return risk signal without recommendation (still persisted as a partial AiSuggestion so it gets a suggestionId).\\n  - Inject WeeklyCommitRepository to load commits for the plan.\\n  - Inject AiSuggestionService for persisting recommendation audit rows.\\n- Create backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/dto/PlanRecommendationResponse.java — API response DTO. Must include a UUID suggestionId field so the frontend can reference it for AiFeedbackButtons and per-recommendation dismissal.\\n- Add endpoints to AiController.java:\\n  - GET /api/ai/plans/{planId}/recommendations with X-Actor-User-Id header → returns List<PlanRecommendationResponse> by reading persisted rows (stable IDs, no regeneration).\\n  - POST /api/ai/plans/{planId}/recommendations/refresh with X-Actor-User-Id header → triggers generateAndPersistRecommendations(), deletes stale rows, persists fresh ones, returns the new list.